roduct manager is easy, but explaining this to someone who has never heard about UX is difficult, let alone explaining it to my nephew or grandpa! This blog is my personal experience of explaining my job as a UX Researcher to a 27 years old friend, my 7 years nephew, and my lovely 73 years old grandpa. Without further ado, letâ€™s get into how I would explain what UX Research is.</p><figure class="lj lk ll lm ln lo fw fx paragraph-image"><div role="button" tabindex="0" class="lp lq at lr v ls"><div class="fw fx li"><div class="lx s at ly"><div class="lz ma s"><div class="fe lt et fh fd lh v lu lv lw"><img alt="A grandpa and a grandson" class="et fh fd lh v mb mc ae" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/40/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm?q=20" width="700" height="1050"/></div><img alt="A grandpa and a grandson" class="fe lt et fh fd lh v c" width="700" height="1050"/><noscript><img alt="A grandpa and a grandson" class="et fh fd lh v" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm" width="700" height="1050" srcSet="https://miro.medium.com/max/552/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm 276w, https://miro.medium.com/max/1104/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm 552w, https://miro.medium.com/max/1280/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm 640w, https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0*QUw77qIno4iD1jFm 700w" sizes="700px"/></noscript></div></div></div></div><figcaption class="md me fy fw fx mf mg bf b bg bh dx">Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@dino_97?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" class="el mh" rel="noopener nofollow">Nourdine Diouane</a> on <a href="https://unsplash.com?utm_source=medium&amp;utm_medium=referral" class="el mh" rel="noopener nofollow">Unsplash</a></figcaption></figure></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><h1 id="b3a6" class="mp mq gq bf mr ms mt jz mu mv mw kc mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk hn">Me and my 7 years old nephew</h1><p id="4a57" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nl jz ka hs nm kc kd ke nn kg kh ki no kk kl km np ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me:</strong> My job is about making technologies like websites, mobile apps, and console games more fun. Can you name some games you play?</p><p id="604e" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">M<span id="rmm"><span id="rmm">y</span></span> 7 years old nephew</strong>: <em class="nv">Fortnite, Just Dance, Minecraftâ€¦</em></p><p id="084c" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me</strong>: Taking Fortnite as an example, you can see there are a lot of different options you can go to when going to the game. Suppose I want to find information about armors. How would I go about finding that?</p><blockquote class="nw nx ny"><p id="4dfa" class="jv jw nv jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">[Waiting for my nephew to answer]</strong></p></blockquote><p id="646e" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn">Me: Yes! Now, if youâ€™d never played Fortnite, how would you know that was the right place for finding armors?</p><blockquote class="nw nx ny"><p id="3752" class="jv jw nv jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">[Waiting for some answers]</strong></p></blockquote><p id="2d80" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me</strong>: Exactly! You noticed the {picture of the armor}.</p><p id="c884" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">What I do at my job is to see if a website or game is working well. I talk to a lot of people to ask them questions about how they use technology.</strong></p><blockquote class="jj"><p id="fdd4" class="jk jl gq bf jm jn nz oa ob oc od jt dx">Kids are smarter than what you think, they quickly get it. You just need to give them examples from mobile or console that they play. Then they immidetaly give you examples of how difficult it is to sign out, collect more diamonds, or change something in the settings of their favorite game. They might even ask you to fix it because they know itâ€™s part of your job!</p></blockquote></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><h1 id="d852" class="mp mq gq bf mr ms mt jz mu mv mw kc mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk hn">Me and my 27 years old friend</h1><p id="189c" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nl jz ka hs nm kc kd ke nn kg kh ki no kk kl km np ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me:</strong> User Experience Researchers work with designers to improve the experience of the users of a product. We adopt different research methods to figure out problems and design opportunities. Doing so, We reveal information that can be fed into the design process.</p><p id="079a" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">My 27 years old friend</strong>: <em class="nv">Ah ok, so itâ€™s like market research but more specific?</em></p><p id="3f58" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me</strong>: Wellâ€¦no. Market research is important and it provides information about the brand and business performance in the market while UX Research is digging deeper by observing how users work with a product, how the product meets user needs. For example, figuring out that you are frustrated with how Microsoft Teams works lies under my job as a UX Researcher and not a market researcher.</p><p id="57e1" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">My 27 years old friend</strong>: <em class="nv">Oookaaayâ€¦ I think I got it!</em></p><blockquote class="jj"><p id="3fcb" class="jk jl gq bf jm jn nz oa ob oc od jt dx">Microsoft products make the best cases for explaining UX and UX Research! Just go with a Microsoft product example if you are explaining your job to an adult.</p></blockquote></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><h1 id="fad5" class="mp mq gq bf mr ms mt jz mu mv mw kc mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk hn">Me and my 73 years old grandpa</h1><p id="ada3" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nl jz ka hs nm kc kd ke nn kg kh ki no kk kl km np ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">Me:</strong> Grandpa,<br/>There is a system used in hospitals to keep the patientsâ€™ history in computers rather than documenting everything on paper. We watched a reception at the register and saw that he wrote down the requests on a piece of paper because he was juggling one patient on the phone and one in-person. Afterward, he entered those things from the paper into the system.</p><blockquote class="nw nx ny"><p id="13b7" class="jv jw nv jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn">We realized they needed to be able to easily switch between patientâ€™s information on the system, in order to avoid having to write stuff down and stay in the system. So we created an interface to make the experience of the receptionists better, now they can quickly switch from one patient to the next, and not have to use paper.</p></blockquote><p id="dc7e" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><strong class="jx gr">My 73 years old grandpa</strong>: <em class="nv">Ok, that makes sense, thatâ€™s why you call yourself an Experience Researcher.</em></p></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><h1 id="e6e6" class="mp mq gq bf mr ms mt jz mu mv mw kc mx my mz na nb nc nd ne nf ng nh ni nj nk hn"><strong class="ci">Moral of the story</strong></h1><p id="bd1a" class="jv jw gq jx b hp nl jz ka hs nm kc kd ke nn kg kh ki no kk kl km np ko kp jt gj hn">Kids are smarter than what we think, they quickly get it. So do adults and elderly people. All we have to do is to give a good example that makes sense for them. And as always, examples from Microsoft products always help, be it Xbox games for kids or MS software (Teams/Word) for adults.</p></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><h2 id="4307" class="oe mq gq bf mr of og hr mu oh oi hu mx hv oj hx nb hy ok ia nf ib ol id nj om hn">More UX Reads:</h2><blockquote class="nw nx ny"><p id="8a7b" class="jv jw nv jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><a class="el mh" rel="noopener" href="/19-things-ux-researchers-hate-to-hear-explained-with-gifs-445f06792370"><strong class="jx gr"><em class="gq">19 things you shouldnâ€™t say to a UX researcher (explained with GIFs)</em></strong></a></p><p id="a547" class="jv jw nv jx b hp nq jz ka hs nr kc kd ke ns kg kh ki nt kk kl km nu ko kp jt gj hn"><a class="el mh" rel="noopener" href="/the-usability-issue-that-caused-1-death-and-38-injuries-97911dfa5c7f"><strong class="jx gr"><em class="gq">The usability issue that caused 1 death and 38 injuries</em></strong></a></p></blockquote></div></div></section><div class="n p db mi mj mk" role="separator"><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn mo"></span><span class="ml iq ca mm mn"></span></div><section class="gj gk gl du gm"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay gn ba v"><figure class="lj lk ll lm ln lo fw fx paragraph-image"><div class="fw fx on"><img alt="" class="v lb oo" src="https://miro.medium.com/max/188/0*p52TpfFyP52JA08x" width="94" height="40" role="presentation"/></div><figcaption class="md me fy fw fx mf mg bf b bg bh dx">The UX Collective donates US$1 for each article published in our platform. This story contributed to <a href="https://www.bayareablackdesigners.com/" class="el mh" rel="noopener nofollow">Bay Area Black Designers</a>: a professional development community for Black people who are digital designers and researchers in the San Francisco Bay Area. By joining together in community, members share inspiration, connection, peer mentorship, professional development, resources, feedback, support, and resilience. Silence against systemic racism is not an option. Build the design community you believe in.</figcaption></figure></div></div></section></div></article><div class="fe gi ff ov v ow fh ot ox" data-test-id="post-sidebar"><div class="n p"><div class="au av aw ax ay az ba v"><div class="oy n ao"><div class="gi"><div><div class="oz s"><div class="pa s"><a href="https://medium.com/@hosseinraspberry?source=post_sidebar--------------------------post_sidebar-----------" class="el em ce cf cg ch ci cj ck bq en eo cl ep eq" rel="noopener"><h2 class="bf mr dn bh gp hn gj">Hossein Raspberry</h2></a></div><div class="pb s"><p class="bf b bg bh dx">Researcher | Storyteller | Foodie | I love people and words ðŸ‡­ðŸ‡ºðŸ‡ºðŸ‡¸ðŸ‡®ðŸ‡·â€” On Medium since August 2020</p></div><div class="pc n">